         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Well Narben, if thats the way they implemented it, they screwed up. You are implying that we all load the new animations for all races even though we have them off? (the old animation != the new for each race) Also, are we loading horses and mage pets when we have them off? This seems ridiculous to me. Why load something we wont use?<BR> <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>No, only one set of files is loaded depending on which choice you make (luclin ON or OFF). There are 2 sets of global files and the appropriate character animations are pulled out of each and loaded into memory depending on which you've chosen to view.</P><P>Necros have 2 problems.<BR>One is that unlike mages we had 2 different pets and now only have one. Mages have 4 old pets and 4 new pets giving a simple yes/no choice. You can't add necro pets as an on/off choice of model without loading both of the old models thereby taking up extra space in the global file. <BR>Two is that our skeleton model is used for every basic human skeleton in the game. If they did return one of the old models, ie dark bone, then every basic skeleton in the game would use that look too. And lets face it, the average non necro couldn't give a crap what a skeleton looks like as long as it's identifiable as a skeleton. There's no incentive for Verant to add a switch to skeleton models that would only be utilised by necros and SK's</P><P></P><P>Narben the Gnome Gnecro<BR>Colleague of Sanctuary<BR>Luclin server<BR>"Find your own damn witty comment"<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
