         Narben:</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>There are 2 sets of global files and the appropriate character animations are pulled out of each and loaded into memory depending on which you've chosen to view.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>So why isnt this an option for old vs new necro pet? </P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>One is that unlike mages we had 2 different pets and now only have one. Mages have 4 old pets and 4 new pets giving a simple yes/no choice. You can't add necro pets as an on/off choice of model without loading both of the old models thereby taking up extra space in the global file.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>You telling me there are a fixed AMOUNT of slots in the file, ie 200 models? Or, each model takes say 4kb memory to load, and you can only have 1mb allocated for the global file? (theoretical values, just for example). If first is true they actually "nerfed" us (if you can nerf a class graphically :P), it just makes no sense. I remember them talking about adding jack'o'lanters and more to the global files, maybe time to remove them, or think how important it is to have dragons in the global file. If the latter is true, its not very hard to go around. I would also think the new models takes alot more memory to load, which means 2 old pets vs 1 new pet might actually be quite equal in size.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>And lets face it, the average non necro couldn't give a crap what a skeleton looks like as long <BR>as it's identifiable as a skeleton. There's no incentive for Verant to add a switch to skeleton models <BR>that would only be utilised by necros and SK's.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>How many uses the new models (races) now? They take up alot memory to load and decreases framerate. The new skeleton also has bigger poly count and decreases framerate too. With 50+ people on raids you want to optimize your FPS as much as possible, so people are using old models if you havent got a very highend computer. The new pet is also alot harder to target then the old pet.</P><P>Regards,</P><P><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20321" target="_blank">Drachan<BR>Warlock of Innoruuk<BR>Antonius Bayle</a></center></P><P>Edited by - Yrsel on 06/17/2002  08:08:37</P><P>Edited by - Yrsel on 06/17/2002  08:10:08<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
